instruction:
Find $a+b+c$, given that $x+y\neq -1$ and  \begin{align*}
ax+by+c&=x+7,\\
a+bx+cy&=2x+6y,\\
ay+b+cx&=4x+y.
\end{align*}

llama2_fine_tuned_on_chatgpt_solution:
we have $x+y\neq -1$, so $x+y=1$ and $x+y=2$ and $x+y=3$.  we can use the first equation to find $a+b+c$:
\begin{align*}
a+b+c&=x+7\\
&=1+7\\
&=8
\end{align*}
so $a+b+c=8$.  we can use the second equation to find $a+b+c$:
\begin{align*}
a+b+c&=2x+6y\\
&=1+6(2)\\
&=8
\end{align*}
so $a+b+c=8$.  we can use the third equation to find $a+b+c$:
\begin{align*}
a+b+c&=4x+y\\
&=1+4(2)\\
&=8
\end{align*}
so $a+b+c=8$.  therefore, $a+b+c=8$.

